description:
Recently sold: $475,000. *** Must see 3D Tour at:  www.5316chateau.com ***

Exceptional home in the sought-after Hale neighborhood. Steps to Lake Nokomis! This charming home combines classic elegance with modern design and amenities. The main floor is bright and open with formal and informal spaces throughout.

Just off the front foyer is a large living room with woodburning fireplace. The living room opens to an amazing 3 season porch with a beautifully painted floor and vaulted wood ceilings. Adjacent to the living room is a formal dining room with tech lighting. From the dining room is a hall that leads to 2 main floor bedrooms and a full bathroom with separate tub and shower ? beautifully tiled throughout. The shower is handicap accessible and one of the bedrooms features a washer dryer unit within the closet. Truly ? one level living! The main level continues with an amazing addition beyond the original 1926 foundation. The kitchen is well appointed and opens to a spacious mudroom that accesses the large handicap accessible deck. Also adjacent to the kitchen is an informal dining room and large great room that features a soaring vaulted ceiling with amazing floor to ceiling windows. This addition was well thought out and is a must see for those looking for more space!

The upper level features 2 large bedroom suites with an adjacent walkthrough tiled bathroom that accesses both rooms. Also on the upper level is a spacious loft that would make a great reading area, office or play area.

The partially finished basement is bright and open with a huge family room that is perfect for games and entertaining. This exceptional lower level finishes with the 5th bedroom, ½ bath, 2nd laundry area and plenty of storage!

The backyard area is an amazing oasis. The yard is fully fenced between maintenance free fencing on the property and the neighbors fencing. Entertain with ease using the dedicated grilling area and spacious deck with plenty of space for a large patio table. Last but not least, the 2+ car garage has plenty of space for 2 cars and all the toys!

If you are looking for an amazing home and location ? you have found your next home!

description:
Recently sold: $295,000. Small town feel, big city appeal!

This 1920's home is the perfect combination! 

Would you like a relaxing night outside? Placed on a corner lot, you can relax in your own backyard oasis! Sit in your hot tub, or by your waterfall pond and fire pit. Listen to your speaker system and enjoy the privacy of a fenced in backyard. 
Maybe it is better weather to stay in? Curl up by the wood burning fireplace or play some games downstairs by the bar. Maybe a movie night, utilizing that same speaker system inside. Enjoy three levels of warm and welcoming space, perfect for the entire family or entertaining as well.

Feeling outdoorsy? This neighborhood is a gateway to the greenway biking trail, and short distance from Lake Nokomis, Lake Hiawatha, and Minnehaha Falls. All great places to take advantage of nature in the metro.
Perhaps you want a night out, work downtown or need a vacation? Walk the short distance to the light rail system for easy access to DT Mpls, St. Paul and MSP Airport.


Want that small town feel? Located just blocks to the nearest grocery store, brewery, restaurants and shops. All with friendly merchants that will make you feel like a part of the community. No matter your clients' wants and needs, this home has everything they are looking for!  Upper BR has been used as family room and has so many other options including space to add a bath and make it quite the owners' suite!!! Flex closing and possession options so contact Todd for more info.

description:
Recently sold: $505,000. A classic 3-bedroom, South Minneapolis Tudor featuring beautiful woodwork and many unique features such as a wine cellar, oversized 2-car garage and blooming gardens. The home was built in 1929 and contains 1,983 square feet including finished basement. The first floor features a recently renovated kitchen with stainless steel appliances, quartz countertops, custom lighting and elongated subway tile. The living room features french doors onto the deck, a stone fireplace and gorgeous, custom-made built-in bookshelves. The dining room includes two built-in cabinets, a custom-built radiator cover and a unique chandelier. The second-floor includes a master bedroom suite made up of two former bedrooms and a lovely guest bedroom with custom wallpaper. The suite can easily be converted back to two separate bedrooms with installation of French doors or a wall. The master also has a walk-in closet. A classic, subway tile finishes the renovated bathroom. The refinished basement level features a second bathroom with shower, custom built cabinets that hold a large screen tv, and a wine cellar with iron doors. A laundry and large storage area complete the basement. The property, located on a corner lot, includes an over-sized two-car garage with attic and built in firewood shed. A no-maintenance deck sits just off the back of the house and the backyard is completely fenced in for privacy with no-maintenance material. The entire property contains lovely gardens and perennials that bloom throughout the season. Location, Location, Location! Located in the heart of South Minneapolis, the home is just a block off Minnehaha park with its biking and walking trails connecting you anywhere in the city. 3 blocks away are several popular restaurants such as Turtle Bread, Burrito Mercado, Bagu sushi, and the Town Hall brewpub. Bike shops, a coffee shop, gym, clothing and home furnishings stores complete this neighborhood gem. Lake Nokomis, Minnehaha Falls, downtown Minneapolis, the Mall of America, Target, and other shopping and recreational opportunities are all within a 12 minute drive.

description:
Recently sold: $595,000. FOR SALE BY OWNER (FSBO): Please call us with any inquiries about our property. We're happy to answer your questions. Dave & Tracy @ 612 822 6708. 

An exquisite Mediterranean style home located just across the street from Minnehaha Parkway in south Minneapolis (Shenandoah Terrace neighborhood). The front yard of the home is beautifully landscaped with fabulous views of the Parkway to enjoy.  Biking & walking trails, kayaking on the creek or sipping your morning expresso, while enjoying the fragrances of spring or the colors of autumn, are a part of your everyday lifestyle. 

The backyard has a breathtaking garden with an expansive tiled patio, pergola, gurgling fountains, flowering plants, lush greenery & a cedar privacy fence that provides a perfect opportunity to entertain or rest & relax in a quiet sanctuary where birds & butterflies flitter.

The interior spaces of the home are bright & open with plentiful windows & expansive views of the outdoors that make parkway living a unique experience while preserving a sense of warmth & intimacy within.  The vintage crown moldings, arched door entry, hardwood floors & French windows preserve the craftsmanship of its 1920s heritage.

A cozy remodeled eat-in kitchen featuring recently refinished cabinetry, tumbled tile backsplash & flooring, under counter lighting, an island with granite countertop, ceiling fan & stainless steel appliances is the warm heart of the home. 

A wood-burning fireplace in the living room warms wintry evenings providing a cheery centerpiece for entertaining or a quiet evening with family.  A spacious dining room off the living area overlooks the garden.  Sunrooms on the first & second levels provide inviting alternatives for social gatherings or quietly enjoying the morning or evening light with a book or glass of wine. 

All 3 bedrooms are upstairs on the 2nd level & feature closets done by California Closets to make the most of your space. 

The finished basement has copious amounts of additional storage space, tiled floors, a lovely laundry area & an extra large walk-in cedar closet.  

Upgrades include: kitchen remodel, 3/4 bath remodel, finished basement, ceiling fans, copper gutters, downspouts & crowns, new roof membranes on home & garage, parapet tiles, garage doors, insulation, sheetrock & crank out windows in garage, large tiled patio, pergola, pavers, rock, landscaping, fountains, stonework, cedar privacy fence, LOXON painted stucco & a lined sewer with a 50 year warranty! 

Pet approved! Cats love to bask in the sunny windows while dogs enjoy the great outdoors. The fenced in backyard, combined with the trails, open grassy areas & Minnehaha Creek, provide hours of fun & entertainment for you & your beloved furry companion.

LOCATION, LOCATION, LOCATION! Centrally located in south Minneapolis just minutes from the lakes, restaurants, Mall of America, Minnehaha Falls, the airport & downtown.  A beautiful & meticulously maintained home, breathtaking views & fabulous location; this home has it all. 

ATTENTION:  Unfortunately, our Zestimate is way off because Zillow's Price / Tax information was incorrect. I worked with customer service (at length & with the house deed) to correct the error in the Price History of the home & it has finally been updated. However, the Zestimate # hasn't changed yet to reflect the true value of the home based on the correction.  I was told it may be a long time before it adjusts. Therefore, please disregard the Zestimate # for our home at this time.  Home values, based on the latest Case-Schiller home price index (April 2019) for Minneapolis, have increased 31% since we purchased the home in August 2002 for $470,000. We also added 1,000 finished square feet to the home since our purchase. 

AGENTS:  We have a real estate attorney. Therefore, we request there be no solicitations for representation. We welcome all inquiries from independent buyers & agents representing buyers.

Book a showing before it is gone, this one won't last long!!

Recently sold: $475,000. 4849 Park Ave S, Minneapolis, MN 55417 
4 beds 3 baths 2,540 sq ft 

 This classic Tudor home is meticulously cared for and sits in the desired south Minneapolis Nakomis neighborhood alongside Minnehaha Park/Creek. There are several parks within walking distance. The closest park is 1 block away. This is a great location for active families, but equally suitable for those who enjoy a quiet neighborhood feel. Location of the home allows for a short walk to restaurants, bars, liquor store, coffee shop, bakery, movie theater, animal hospital, and shopping ALL within 2 blocks! This house has old world charm, but with many updates.
What I love about the home
Just 2 blocks from the shops and restaurants of 48th & Chicago. These close amenities along with the close parks and the down to earth feeling make it a great neighborhood. Sledding and outdoor ice rinks are within 3 blocks. It is a very pedestrian friendly neighborhood and a safe place for kids to roam about. The home itself has a great back yard and patio for dining. A ten minute commute to downtown with incredible access to biking trails and just a 1 minute walk to Minnehaha creek for fishing, tubing, and kayak access.

~ 4 bedrooms

description: Recently sold: $370,000.

Recently sold: $381,700. Wonderful home in the desirable Hale school district!  The kids can walk to school!  Open floor plan with hardwood floors throughout.  Plenty of shelves in dining room.  Wood burning FP.  French doors leading to a wonderful deck to entertain on.  Amazing neighbors!

Recently sold: $272,752. Spacious bungalow full of style, charm, and architectural details. Fantastic Nokomis location steps from great restaurants and shops, light rail, Lake Nokomis and Minnehaha Falls parks.
Welcoming front porch. Great light in the bonus sunroom. Gorgeous detailed woodwork, hardwood floors, and 9ft ceilings. Kitchen with lots of cabinets, stainless appliances, and new flooring. The bedrooms have hardwood floors and good-sized closets. Period style in the updated main floor bath. Neutral white tile floors and walls with an in-room storage closet. Great opportunity to finish the upper level. The large space offers potential as another bedroom or additional living area. The lower level is clean and bright with plenty of space. Well updated systems in this home too: High efficiency boiler and new water heater. Nice patio in the back yard for summer BBQs. Two-car garage and a private driveway. You'll love living so close to everything that makes this Nokomis neighborhood so great!

The home features 200 amp panel, surround sound throughout the lower two levels, EcoBee smart thermostat with remote sensor. Plus flat ceilings throughout, stunning hardwood floors, newer mechanicals and windows. Recently remodeled kitchen with HEATED slate flooring, soft close cherry cabinets, undercount lighting and GE Profile stainless steel appliances. Both bathrooms thoughtfully updated with tile flooring brushed nickel fixtures and fresh paint.

description:
Recently sold: $370,000. Fully remodeled Tudor on quiet block in the Minnehaha neighborhood.  With almost 2500 ft2, this is much larger than the typical 1.5 story.  Almost everything updated/remodeled in the last 5 yrs while still maintaining it's original character & charm. 

Updates:  Interior - Fully redone kitchen, basement w/ egress & large br, all 3 full baths including upper master suite.  All new electrical & plumbing.  Recently painted & refinished hardwood floors.  Exterior - New Anderson Renewal windows, all exterior doors including sliding patio door, gutters, hardscape/landscape (sod to be installed before listing) and extensive high end concrete work around the property with sophisticated drainage system not only makes for fantastic patios and curb appeal but eliminates any chance of water intrusion.  No corners cut and it shows.  Ready for new owners to move right in and love it as much as the current ones did for the last 5 yrs.

Call/text/email Reid Lenz, SP Real Estate for private pre-list showing - reidlenz@gmail.com  612.315.9675

Recently sold: $419,000. Very conveniently located in a nice and quiet neighborhood.  Blocks to Light Rail stations, Nokomis Lake and Minnehaha Park.  House is all updated throughout.  Heated oversized 2 car garage is great for car repair and maintenance.

Recently sold: $334,848. Stately Tudor in sought-after Keewaydin!   This gracious and expansive 1800 sf 1.5-story has all the charm you're looking for: lovely oak floors, stone fireplace, panel doors, coved ceilings, formal dining room, eat-in kitchen and tiled full bath. Upstairs, the expansive master bedroom awaits your touch. Finished basement with 3/4 bath offers great spaces for an office, home gym or in-law/airbnb suite. Fully-fenced yard with patio--woof! 2-car garage plus a tuckunder space for tons of storage. Steps from Keewaydin School (grades 3-8)! Walk to Lake Nokomis, the all-new Bossen Field Park, Nokomis Library, Minnehaha Falls, restaurants, coffee shops, Oxendale's grocery and more. Welcome home!

Recently sold: $410,000. Charming sun-filled home with coved ceilings and hardwood floors. Spacious kitchen includes original 36" cabinets, granite countertops and stainless steel appliances. Large living room offers a wood-burning fireplace and bay window. Master suite with private bath, walk-in closet and skylight. Oversized  lower level family room. Great 4-season porch with tile flooring and access to the amazing concrete patio.

Recently sold: $164,900. Hard to find townhouse in the heart of Minnehaha. 2 level corner unit with lots of light and generous room sizes, closet space. Includes in-unit laundry. 2 bedrooms and bathroom up, with kitchen and living areas on first floor. North and east facing with lots of windows. Walk to Minnehaha Falls and the light rail. Updated kitchen and appliances. Private entrance and 1 car garage included. 


New furnace and AC in 2016. New roof in 2018 by Les Jones Roofing.

Recently sold: $400,000. Charming Brick Cape Cod with amazing panoramic views of Diamond Lake. Set up above the lake, giving it a Parkway feel. 3 bedrooms (all on one level), 2 bathrooms, and an oversized 2 car garage.  Two wonderful 4 season rooms, and exceptional natural light throughout the house. Main level wood burning fireplace and hardwood floors. Fully fenced backyard with new landscaping, paver patio, and in-ground sprinkler system. Truly one of the most charming homes you will see! Contact Matt Lill for more information or to schedule an appointment. 612-578-8200. MattLill@EdinaRealty.com

description:
Recently sold: $550,000. This classic Minneapolis Tudor, steps from Minnehaha Creek, has been completely updated. Thoughtful renovations maintained the home's original character while adding modern amenities. Original hardwood floors, coved ceilings and a wood-burning fireplace are among the many preserved architectural details. The main living space flows openly from the entryway, living room, dining room, and updated kitchen. The kitchen features granite counters, enameled cabinets, a marble backsplash, stainless steel appliances, and a breakfast bar. Upstairs in the owner's suite you'll find a private ensuite bathroom, several large closets, and laundry. A fully finished basement includes a non-conforming 5th bedroom. Outside, a new brick paver patio leads to a recently constructed 2-car garage. All of this is topped off by the close proximity to Minnehaha Creek, the Minnehaha Trail, and easy access to Lake Nokomis!
 2019-06-13
